Descripcion_Completa:
What does your job as a Digital Phenotyping Specialist at Rijk Zwaan look like?

Rijk Zwaan develops and sells new vegetable varieties all over the world. In order to select the best plants for further breeding, many trials are carried out worldwide. In order to support further growth in the number of trials and to be able to support decisions with better data, Rijk Zwaan has been focusing on the digital assessment of (plant) material, also known as digital phenotyping, for years. This field is fully in development and we therefore need a Digital Phenotyping Specialist who, based on breeding knowledge and experience, helps our breeding teams to make Digital Phenotyping part of their daily work processes.

As a Digital Phenotyping Specialist, you will work for all vegetables in our locations in Spain (in Almeria, Murcia & El Ejido). Intensive cooperation with colleagues from IT and Breeding Operations is paramount. You will coordinate projects for the development and implementation of Digital Phenotyping at Rijk Zwaan, specifically at our breeding hub in Spain. You are the link to various stakeholders within the organization (also in the Netherlands) and can translate breeding needs into digital solutions.

As a Digital Phenotyping Specialist, you will be involved in:

Planning and coordinating projects in which software solutions and (image analysis) technology improve the processes of breeding;
Supervising the international implementation of Digital Phenotyping solutions at our breeding station in Spain;
Advising on the applicability of commercial hardware and software;
Research into new possibilities and technologies that can be used for Digital Phenotyping;
Continuously improving our image analysis processes so that they support Digital Phenotyping more and more efficiently;
Translating breeders' wishes into concrete proposals for improvement of Digital Phenotyping projects;
Translating and integrating digital data and analyses into the working methods and needs of breeders;
Adoption of Digital Phenotyping and the associated change process within breeding.



What you bring:


You have good communication skills and easily connect with colleagues inside and outside your department. You enjoy working internationally and can function in an integrator role. You are proactive and motivated to learn and improve. In addition, you have experience in leading change processes and your enthusiasm makes it easy to take people along in new developments.

In addition, we can find the following on your resume:

Academic working and thinking level; preferably big data analytics/science background
Knowledge of and experience with breeding;
Affinity with the implementation of hardware and software systems in operational processes.
Fluent in Spanish and English, both spoken and in writing.
Frequent travelling to the Netherlands is a requirement
Experience in project management is welcome

What can you expect from us?

As a Digital Phenotyping Specialist, you will be part of the Breeding Process & Organisation (BP&O) team and located in our breeding hub in Spain. The team consists of specialists in the fields of Genomic Breeding, Data Sciences, Digital Phenotying, process analysis and project management, whose joint task is to improve and optimise the processes and organisation within the breeding of all crops in Rijk Zwaan.

You will work closely with the Applied Image Analysis team. This is a multi-disciplinary team consisting of specialists with knowledge of AI, image analysis, data processing, Digital Phenotyping, software development, breeding and mechanical engineering. You will be given a lot of personal responsibility and the space to help shape your position as you see fit. In addition to an ambitious international working environment where you can work on the latest innovations, we are happy to offer you:

Immediately a permanent contract
A competitive salary based on job level and experience;
Various training opportunities through our Rijk Zwaan Academy and specific IT training courses;

Rijk Zwaan: your new employer?

Rijk Zwaan is an international family business with a people-oriented corporate culture. Rijk Zwaan is at the beginning of the food chain. We develop vegetable varieties and sell the seeds to growers all over the world. From our position, we can and want to contribute to the world's food supply. It's all about growth. The growth of a natural product, which we export worldwide. The growth of our company, which now employs more than 4000 people in more than 30 countries. And above all, the growth of our employees. With us, you get all the space you need to do business and develop yourself.

Interested?


Do you recognize yourself and would you prefer to get started tomorrow? Click on 'Apply' to apply directly. Please send your application to Mar Hernández (Human Resources Advisor).

Because your application will be carefully reviewed by several people, you will receive a response as soon as possible. An assessment and screening are part of the procedure.

How does your job as Client Manager at Rijk Zwaan?

As Client Manager in Spain you work on the support and development of clients and dealers. You build and develop further long-term and trusting relationships with clients at a management, tactical and operational level. You give professional advice and consult customers on Rijk Zwaan products and modern technologies. You track market trends and look for new clients. You work with a professional CRM system and accurately forecast the sales forecasts & results.

Additionally, you are responsible for:

Define the strategy for your clients (Know his position in the chain, Identify potential growth opportunities, create de strategy and translate into a concrete client plan)
Lead client activities (Be the first point of contact for the client and introduce the right specialists at the right time, Identify and develop relationships with key decision makers of the client at all levels, Work across Rijk Zwaan to create custom solutions, Identify strategic partnership opportunities)
Be accountable for the results (Identify sales opportunities and report activities of the competition, make the value of our proposition explicit, be responsible for the collection of overdue payments, deal promptly with potential complaints)
Use RZ systems and tooling for effective international collaboration (CRM, Analys client information, timnely sales forecast)
Take care of communication with relevant stakeholders

What is your added value?

You are based in Almería (Spain) committed to provide a high service level and to maintain the ethics of the company. You take initiative easily and you have a commercial and client-focused approach. You have good analytical skills and are able to think strategically. You are a team-player, have strong communication skills. You keep track of the latest developments in the horticultural industry, an independent self-starter with the ability to set your own goals and agenda in line with the company policy and the local management.

In addition, we can find the following on your resume:

A completed Bachelor’s degree in the field of Agriculture;
7-10 years of relevant work experience in sales and account management in an international environment;
Leadership skills;
Influence and persuasion to lead and manage diverse client teams;
Networking skills – ability to build bridges and connect people;
Willing to travel frequently (both domestic and international)
Project and process management skills;
Good command of written and spoken English language;

What can you expect from us?

As Client Manager you will be part of Rijk Zwaan team. The team work actively on the introduction and supply of Rijk Zwaan varieties in the market.

Besides the international and entrepreneurial work environment, interaction with colleagues from different countries and the opportunity to serve customers with our seeds and services, we are happy to offer you:

permanent contract from the start;
competitive to the market salary based on job level and experience;
various training opportunities through our Rijk Zwaan Academy on personal and professional development;
extensive on-boarding program;

Hagoort & Partners is doing the search for this position and Patrick Westerburger is the contact person.


You can address your application to Patrick Westerburger via the apply button. We will consider your application carefully, which may take some time. You will hear from us as soon as possible.

